venue.name: White Restaurant 三巴旺百米分 @ Sun Plaza

tips.text: Yummy white beehoon!
They sell lots of nick nack childhood snacks too. Had their tehCsiewdai but the taste of the tea was kinda washed down. Maybe cuz done by the new girl so not that nice?
Love the Mexican grilled chicken.
My favourite ice milk tea, ice green milk tea, and ice coffee! Thick enough not to be diluted by the ice. But service can be improved...
Try the bacon aglio olio here, and put lots of cheese!! :)
Super crowded especially dinner time. Rmb to try the cheese cake. I like it very much.. Hahaa
Dinner with Mummy. :-)
The Chawanmushi is a must get staple when you're here!
There's Satay!
Da coffee is nice... Shud try... Make u awake da whole day...
The staffs here are nice and friendly, will always be back here to buy. 
Nice Nasi lemak

venue.name: Old Street Bak Kut Teh 老街肉骨茶

tips.text: Each bread or slice of cake costs $1.10 after 9:30pm.
Cheap yet flavorful satays. They also serve goreng. :)
The noodles are good. It comes with a combo drink as well!
Mince meat U mian is good...but they need to keep the place cleaner!
Classic Banana Split. Fish and chips. Ice cream.
Cheese sausages here are the best!
Soya ice blended w chewy pearls a must try!
All time fav sotong ball!
Best Bak Chor Mee in Sembawang. Order the Mee Kia which is actually like a thinner version of mee pok.
New Chinese/Seafood rest on Admiral Hill. No svc charge. Good - House Special Tofu, Trotter Beehoon (pricey @$15). OK - Spicy Roast Chicken, Superior Sauce Pork Ribs. Lousy - Richard Clayderman CD
Leave to home now
the belly pork here! with tom yum soup is da bomb!
